Content: [telegram] <Regnar> No (re @Caleb: So I‚Äôve read both of those articles but I still feel unclear. If they are new coins, Is it part of the block reward from mining?)

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Regnar> The rewards are not part of consensus or mining

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Regnar> Proof of stake requires you to have a wallet open and "staking". Komodo does not do this, KMD is equihash PoW. The rewards are different, they have no affect on consensus or mining.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Regnar> Best not to try and fit Rewards into a bucket like PoS. Yes they both result in you having more coins, but they are fundamentally different in what they actually do to obtain them. This is why we actively correct people when they refer to it as staking. Even Binance makes this mistake. But it is NOT staking.
